headline: Exclusive-Amazon, Walmart shareholder pushes firms to report impact of Trump's immigration policies
summary: A union-aligned investment group sent letters to Amazon, Walmart and Alphabet on Wednesday, asking how U.S. President Donald Trump's immigration ​policies were impacting their finances and supply chains, according to the documents seen by Reuters.  SOC Investment ‌Group owns less than 1% of each of the companies, which include some of the top recipients of H-1B visa petition approvals ‌for skilled foreign professionals.  It wants the companies to show how they will navigate Trump's $100,000 fee structure for new visa approvals.
